01/07/2004
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- Judge Richard May, who headed the trial of Slobodan Milosevic until earlier this year, has died at the age of 65, the war crimes tribunal announced Thursday (1 July). 
The cause of death was not released. 
May resigned from the UN tribunal at The Hague earlier this year, citing health reasons. 
He oversaw the lengthy first phase of Milosevic's trial on charges of war crimes and genocide. 
(BBC World - 01/07/04)
